<TITLE> EU, US say negotiated Kosovo solution not possible </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 UNITED NATIONS, Dec 20 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - EU states and the United States said on Wednesday the potential for a negotiated solution on Kosovo was exhausted after the UN Security Council failed to bridge divides on the breakaway Serbian province. Serbia, backed by Russia, called on the Security Council to back further negotiations. "It's clear in our view that more negotiations in this or any other format will not make a difference," a joint EU and US statement said. "The potential for a negotiated solution is now exhausted," the statement said, adding that the European Union was ready to take the lead in charting Kosovo's future. Russian ambassador Vitaly Churkin said there was still room for negotiation. "Any move towards unilateral independence would clearly be outside the limits of international law," he told reporters after the Security Council meeti
